  <data name="generalInfo" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>This auction allows you to bid for different items that are showcased on the home page.
Each bidder can see the current price at the time of the auction and the price gets updated every three (3) seconds. If a bidder bids within that time-span and they don't have the updated price yet, they will see a message informing them that the price has updated and the bidder can proceed with the bid once more once they have the updated price of the item. This warning only shows up in the details page of the item.
From the home page, bidders can only place minimal bids. 
From the details page of an item, a bidder can input any value that is higher than the current price at the time plus the added amount of the minimal price increase
(that can be different for each individual item).</value>
  </data>
