  <data name="instructionsInfo" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>From the home page, you can only place minimal bids on an item.
You are not warned if the price increases within the time-span of three (3) seconds on the home page, but you are warned on the details page of the particular item.
You can also withdraw your bid in placed it by mistake, only if you're not the only bidder.
Once you open the details page, there will be color indicators highlighting information and icons highlighting whenever the price gets updated.
If you're the latest bidder of the item, the info icon's color is going to be blue, otherwise it's going to appear yellow.

When you place a bid the price is gonna glow blue for some time and show the value of the bid you put.

When you withdraw your bid, the price is gonna glow yellow for some time and it's value is gonna go back to the highest value that was bid by other bidders.

You can't place bids with an amount that's lower than the sum of the current price and the minimal price increment amount.
All the info is given within the details page, together with the minimum value you can bid.
If you put an amount lower than that value, the bid button will be disabled and you're not able to place a bid.
That will also be indicated by the red colored amount in your input.

Once the amount is right as stated above, the color of the numbers in your input are going to go back to black and the bid button will be enabled, allowing you to place a bid.
If within that time you do not place a bid and the price gets increased, you will have to change your input value accordingly.</value>
  </data>
